List of the main macros to run simulations described in chapter 7,
Stacking faults 
################################################################################

Macros k_*.mac are the corresponding KUPLOT macros to create a plot of 
the structure and/or intensity distribution

################################################################################


stack.01.mac              Simulates a simple sequence of stacking faults

stack.h0l.mac             Simulates growth faults and caclulates the 
                          intensity in the h0l layer
                          k_h0l.mac

stack.growth.h0l_rod.mac  Simulates growth faults and caclulates the
                          intensity along the 10L rod
                          k_stack.growth.10l_rod.mac

stack.def.mac             Simulates deformation faults and caclulates the
                          intensity along the 10L rod
                          k_stack.def.10l_rod.mac

4h.mac                    Creates a perfect 4H structure
                          k_4h.mac

stack.sort.mac            Simulates a disordered 4H sequence Primary algorithm
                          k_sort.mac

stack.sortvec.mac         Simulates a disordered 4H sequence, Sorting of 
                          interlayer vectors
                          k_sortvec.mac 

cleanup.mac               Removes ALL simulated structure, plotfiles,
                          intensites etc.
